article.headline: Lafayette 82, Columbia 73
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Rob Dill scored 12 of his 18 points in the second half to help Lafayette beat Columbia 82-73 Saturday night. Pat Betley, Justin DeBerry, Winston Davis and Marcus Harley each added 14 points for the Leopards (9-3), who broke a two-game losing streak. Dodson Worthington had a career-high 19 points for the Lions (3-8), who lost for the fourth time in five games and the 26th time in their last 29 games. Columbia led four times in the first half, never by more than three points, and Lafayette broke the game's eighth and final tie with a 3-point shot that put the Leopards in front 25-22 with 8:58 remaining in the half. Lafayette led by as much 11, 60-49 in the second half. Maurice Murphy did not score for the Lions, but had a career-best 14 assists, while Jeremiah Boswell scored 14 points, Dragutin Kravic 13 and Matt Preston 12.
